author: Kosaku Narioka
title: Nikkei May Trade in Rangebound; China Trade Data Eyed
text: [Dow Jones] Japanese stocks may trade in rangebound, weighed on by concerns about a further slowdown in the Chinese economy, while speculation for continued accommodative policy in the U.S. will likely support stocks. Market participants are paying attention to Chinaâ€™s trade data to be released later in the day. Oil prices dropped Monday after the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries reported that its output rose to a more-than-three-year high last month, pointing to supply glut. Meanwhile, speculation is growing that Federal Reserve will maintain its easy policy stance given potential downside risks...
